# PRD Traceability Rule

- Every new or edited requirement must keep an ID format (`FR-*`, `NFR-*`, `TC*`, or `UAT-*`).
- Keep requirement text testable: one behavior per bullet, clear trigger and expected outcome.
- For each major feature update, ensure consistency across:
  - feature requirements
  - edge-case handling
  - security/KVKK constraints
  - test acceptance criteria
- Do not change numeric constraints (timing, limits, capacities) without explicit reason.
- Mark assumptions clearly if implementation details are still unknown.

# Domain Constraints

- Maintain offline-first behavior for critical flows.
- Preserve privacy-by-default: minimal location usage, protected personal data, no unnecessary PII logging.
